      "id": "m6rlxhp4",
      "questionNumber": 7,
      "questionText": "<p>Identify correct conversion during acidic hydrolysis from the following :</p>\n<p>(A) starch gives galactose.</p>\n<p>(B) cane sugar gives equal amount of glucose and fructose.</p>\n<p>(C) milk sugar gives glucose and galactose.</p>\n<p>(D) amylopectin gives glucose and fructose.</p>\n<p>(E) amylose gives only glucose.</p>\n<p>Choose the <b>correct </b>answer from the options given below :</p>",
      "options": [
        "<p>(A), (B) and (C) only</p>",
        "<p>(B), (C) and (D) only</p>",
        "<p>(B), (C) and (E) only</p>",
        "<p>(C), (D) and (E) only</p>"
      ],
      "correctOption": 2,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "topic": "carbohydrates",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "<p>(A) Starch $\\xrightarrow{\\mathrm{H}^{+} / \\mathrm{H}_2 \\mathrm{O}}$ Glucose</p>\n<p>(B) $$\\mathrm{\\mathop {Cane\\,sugar}\\limits_{(Sucrose)} \\buildrel {{H^ + }/{H_2}O} \\over\n \\longrightarrow \\mathop {glu\\cos e}\\limits_{50\\% } \\, + \\mathop {fructose}\\limits_{50\\% }}$$</p>\n<p>(C) $$\\mathrm{\\mathop {Milk\\,sugar}\\limits_{(Lactose)} \\buildrel {{H^ + }/{H_2}O} \\over\n \\longrightarrow glu\\cos e\\, + \\,galactose}$$</p>\n<p>(D) Amylopectin $\\xrightarrow{\\mathrm{H}^{+} / \\mathrm{H}_2 \\mathrm{O}}$ Glucose</p>\n<p>(E) Amylose $\\xrightarrow{\\mathrm{H}^{+} / \\mathrm{H}_2 \\mathrm{O}}$ Glucose</p>\n<p>So, correct options are B, C and E only</p>",
      "section": "A",
      "instruction": "",
      "examSource": "jee-main"
    },
    {
      "id": "m9elqyz2",
      "questionNumber": 8,
      "questionText": "<p>Given below are two statements :</p><p><b>Statement (I) :</b> On hydrolysis, oligo peptides give rise to fewer number of α-amino acids while proteins give rise to a large number of β-amino acids.</p><p><b>Statement (II) :</b> Natural proteins are denatured by acids which convert the water soluble form of fibrous proteins to their water insoluble form.</p><p>In the light of the above statements, choose the <b>most appropriate answer</b> from the options given below :</p>",
      "options": [
        "<p><b>Statement I</b> is incorrect but <b>Statement II</b> is correct</p>",
        "<p>Both <b>Statement I</b> and <b>Statement II</b> are incorrect</p>",
        "<p>Both <b>Statement I</b> and <b>Statement II</b> are correct</p>",
        "<p><b>Statement I</b> is correct but <b>Statement II</b> is incorrect</p>"
      ],
      "correctOption": 1,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "topic": "proteins-and-enzymes",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "<p>When oligopeptides undergo hydrolysis, they yield a small number of α-amino acids. In contrast, proteins do not produce β-amino acids upon hydrolysis. Thus, Statement I is incorrect.</p>\n<p>Furthermore, natural proteins, when subjected to denaturation by acids, do not convert fibrous proteins from a water-soluble to a water-insoluble form, as fibrous proteins are inherently not water-soluble. Therefore, Statement II is also incorrect.</p>\n<p>In conclusion, both Statement I and Statement II are incorrect.</p>",
      "section": "A",
      "instruction": "",
      "examSource": "jee-main"
    },
